Orlando Pirates have confirmed it  has reached an agreement with Bidvest Wits regarding the signing of midfielder Xolani Mlambo. Pirates said: “Orlando Pirates Football Club is delighted to announce that it has reached an agreement with Bidvest Wits for the signing of midfielder Xolani Mlambo. The deal is subject to a medical.” The Buccaneers said further announcements regarding the signing of new players to bolster the squad, as the Absa Premiership season enters its final stretch, would be made soon. Mlambo joined Bidvest Wits from Chippa United in the 2016-17 PSL campaign. -TNA Reporter